14:25.064 --> 14:26.862
- It was '35, Al.
-'35.

14:26.999 --> 14:28.990
Yeah, yup, WP-

14:32.171 --> 14:34.037
I just don't know, Richard.

14:34.173 --> 14:36.198
- Kids.
- Yeah, kids.

14:36.342 --> 14:37.969
Try to save them a little hurt,

14:38.111 --> 14:39.943
you give them the benefit
of your experience.

14:40.079 --> 14:41.376
Well, they won't listen.

14:41.514 --> 14:44.484
No, they got to go out and
find things out for themselves.

14:44.617 --> 14:45.413
Never changes.

14:45.551 --> 14:47.076
Children just do not listen

14:47.220 --> 14:48.688
to their parents today.

14:48.821 --> 14:51.119
I remember the first time
I didn't listen to you.

14:51.257 --> 14:53.282
Mm. Oh, wasn't that the time

14:53.426 --> 14:56.396
with the girl with the big,
uh... uh, angora sweater?

14:56.529 --> 14:59.021
You better believe it.

14:59.165 --> 15:02.692
Yeah. I didn't think
you'd listen to me on that one.

15:06.072 --> 15:07.471
Yeah.

15:07.607 --> 15:09.439
Listen, Richard, maybe

15:09.575 --> 15:11.304
if-if you had a talk
with Joanie, huh?

15:11.444 --> 15:13.913
Dad, they won't listen
to older brothers, either.

15:15.648 --> 15:17.639
Hey.

15:22.155 --> 15:23.452
How you guys 110N197

15:23.589 --> 15:25.023
What you doing here, Mr. C?

15:25.158 --> 15:27.627
You getting some fudge ripple
for your family, huh?

15:27.760 --> 15:31.060
♪ Ah, ooh, wah... ♪

15:31.197 --> 15:34.895
