15:36.736 --> 15:39.137
♪ Wah, wah ♪

15:39.272 --> 15:41.741
♪ Wah, ooh, wah... ♪

15:41.874 --> 15:42.807
You're both staring.

15:42.942 --> 15:44.603
Is there a hair out of place?

15:44.744 --> 15:47.236
Just tell me which one...
What numb... what number?

15:48.915 --> 15:50.405
He numbers his hair?

15:50.550 --> 15:51.881
Uh, I'll explain that later.
Fonz?

15:52.018 --> 15:53.679
- FONZIE: Yeah.
- Uh, this is about Joanie.

15:53.820 --> 15:57.848
Hey, shortcake.
How is the apple of my eye?

15:57.990 --> 15:59.583
Your apple is smoking.

15:59.725 --> 16:01.159
♪ Ooh, wah... ♪

16:01.294 --> 16:03.228
Joanie is smoking cigarettes?

16:03.362 --> 16:05.160
- Yup.
- I'm afraid so, Fonz.

16:05.298 --> 16:06.663
Who's selling 'em to her?

16:06.799 --> 16:08.631
I'll shove the butts
right up his nose.

16:08.768 --> 16:12.136
Oh, Fonz,
you can't punch out everybody

16:12.271 --> 16:13.830
who sells cigarettes
in Milwaukee.

16:13.973 --> 16:15.998
- You want to bet?
- RICHIE: Fonz.

16:16.142 --> 16:18.042
- FONZIE: What, what? -No. Well,
there's no time for that.

16:18.177 --> 16:19.645
Yeah, we-we got to do
something right now.

16:19.779 --> 16:22.680
All right. All right, you guys
leave it up to me, all right?

16:22.815 --> 16:25.477
I mean, after all,
Joanie is, uh, family, you know.

16:25.618 --> 16:28.451
I mean, she's my number one
chick, right?

16:28.588 --> 16:31.114
If she don't stop smoking...

16:31.257 --> 16:33.055
Whoa.

16:33.192 --> 16:35.058
I mean, you know, I...
(stammering)

16:35.194 --> 16:38.323
Whoa!

16:40.967 --> 16:44.995
A two-whoa talk.

16:45.137 --> 16:47.970
Mm. Yes, but will she listen?

16:52.678 --> 16:54.669
(birds singing)

16:55.715 --> 16:57.274
(knocking)

16:57.416 --> 17:00.750
Come in.

17:00.887 --> 17:02.480
Fonzie?

17:02.622 --> 17:04.521
What's shaking, shortcake?

17:04.656 --> 17:07.490
Well, this is the first time
you've seen my room. How come?

17:07.627 --> 17:09.253
Oh, I-l figure
I'd be a neighbor,

17:09.395 --> 17:10.624
you know, real friendly like.

17:10.762 --> 17:12.321
I was just passing
down the corridor.

17:12.464 --> 17:15.025
I thought I'd stop in,
say hello, you know.

17:15.166 --> 17:17.295
- Hey, that's great Elvis, huh?
- Mm-hmm.

17:17.435 --> 17:19.301
Number two Elvis, hey?
That's even better, huh?

17:19.438 --> 17:20.666
Bobby Darin.

17:20.806 --> 17:22.604
♪ Splish splash, I was... ♪

17:22.742 --> 17:24.267
Are you nutso, smoking?!

17:24.410 --> 17:28.074
All right, Fonzie, I'm through
with all the lectures.

17:28.214 --> 17:30.148
Hey, I don't lecture.

17:30.283 --> 17:32.081
I'm just gonna ask you
one simple question,

17:32.218 --> 17:33.743
and then listen.

17:33.886 --> 17:36.480
You really like to smoke?

17:36.622 --> 17:39.421
Yeah. There's nothing
like a good ciggy.

17:39.559 --> 17:41.118
You know, light up
with friends,

17:41.260 --> 17:44.195
relax, a few laughs. (laughs)

17:44.330 --> 17:48.426
A couple more of those and, uh,
your nose is gonna grow.

17:48.568 --> 17:50.195
All right, it's the Magnets.

17:50.336 --> 17:53.271
They're the most popular club
at Jefferson.

17:53.406 --> 17:55.841
Who do you think
made them so popular?

17:57.476 --> 18:00.537
Well... I'm in with the Magnets,

18:00.680 --> 18:02.273
and-and most of 'em smoke,
and...

18:02.415 --> 18:04.042
And you're afraid
that if you don't,

18:04.183 --> 18:06.277
they're going to dump you
and call you chicken.

18:06.419 --> 18:08.148
That's not it, Fonzie.

18:08.287 --> 18:09.755
I'm a high school junior.

18:09.889 --> 18:11.050
(gasps)

18:11.190 --> 18:13.386
I beg your pardon.

18:13.526 --> 18:15.460
Sit down for a minute.

18:15.595 --> 18:17.563
Let me tell you something.

18:17.697 --> 18:21.463
The hardest thing to do is
to do what you want to do.

18:21.601 --> 18:24.627
You know what a breeze it is
to join the crowd,

18:24.770 --> 18:27.000
be led around by your nose?

18:27.139 --> 18:30.973
You ain't nobody till you do
what you want to do.

18:31.110 --> 18:33.078
But I want to be in this club.

18:33.212 --> 18:34.839
Well, let me put it another way.

18:34.981 --> 18:36.312
Smoking ain't cool.

18:36.449 --> 18:38.781
The Magnets are cool.

18:40.152 --> 18:42.314
My humility usually
don't permit me

18:42.455 --> 18:44.617
to ask this particular question.

18:44.757 --> 18:48.694
Who is the coolest of cool?

18:48.828 --> 18:49.886
Well, you are.

18:50.029 --> 18:52.020
Yeah, that's true. (laughs)

18:54.033 --> 18:56.798
Now, if the Fonz don't smoke,

18:56.936 --> 18:59.200
what does that tell you
about smoking?

18:59.338 --> 19:00.863
That the Fonz doesn't smoke.

19:01.007 --> 19:02.873
But some of the cool kids do.

19:03.009 --> 19:05.808
You gonna give up
smoking or not?

19:05.945 --> 19:07.811
Well, I don't know, Fonzie.

19:07.947 --> 19:10.075
All right, end of convo.

19:10.216 --> 19:12.116
- JOANIE: Fonz?
- Yeah, what?

19:12.251 --> 19:16.085
If I don't smoke,
the Magnets will dump me.

19:20.893 --> 19:23.624
Let me plant two things
in your brain.

19:23.763 --> 19:26.892
You're my favorite shortcake.

19:27.033 --> 19:29.627
And number two--
if you don't stop smoking,

19:29.769 --> 19:31.828
your body is gonna dump you.

19:31.971 --> 19:34.872
And I'm crazy about you.

19:35.007 --> 19:36.998
Whoa.

19:49.388 --> 19:52.050
Well, guys,
how's the chinchilla business?

19:52.191 --> 19:53.784
They gave it up
when they found out

19:53.926 --> 19:56.361
you have to kill 'em
to get the skins.

19:56.495 --> 19:58.190
They thought
they would just shed.

19:58.330 --> 19:59.991
(Potsie chuckles)

20:00.132 --> 20:02.191
I was gonna shave 'em.
(chuckles)

20:02.334 --> 20:05.065
But it's tough to make
a chinchilla go like this.

20:05.204 --> 20:06.865
(laughter)

20:07.006 --> 20:09.498
I still got it,
even in big business.

20:09.642 --> 20:12.839
So, anyway, they're, uh...
they're into greeting cards now.

20:12.978 --> 20:14.946
That's right, Al.
We got 'em for all occasions.

20:15.081 --> 20:16.207
How many do you want?

20:16.348 --> 20:19.113
Well, I'll take one
for Lincoln's birthday.

20:19.251 --> 20:20.741
Lincoln's dead.

20:20.886 --> 20:24.550
Sam Lincoln is dead?

20:24.690 --> 20:26.886
I just saw him this morning.

20:27.026 --> 20:29.495
Well, you never know.

20:34.166 --> 20:36.897
So, Joanie, you're in charge
of decorations for this weekend.

20:37.036 --> 20:38.902
Right. I've got a great idea.

20:39.038 --> 20:40.699
Salute to the varsity.

20:40.840 --> 20:42.808
We get the whole team
and a huge cake

20:42.942 --> 20:44.239
and have 'em pop out of it.

20:44.376 --> 20:46.743
Great idea. Hey, wait.

20:46.879 --> 20:49.644
That means there will be
two guys for each girl.

20:49.782 --> 20:51.807
Uh-huh, I know. (laughs)

20:52.852 --> 20:54.479
Guys.

20:54.620 --> 20:55.849
- Hey, Fonz.
- Hi, Fonz.

20:55.988 --> 20:57.080
No date tonight?

20:57.223 --> 20:58.816
Wash your mouth out.

20:59.892 --> 21:00.882
RALPH:
Hey, Fonz,

21:01.026 --> 21:02.323
we're in the greeting card
business now.

21:02.461 --> 21:04.429
- Want to buy some?
- Yeah.

21:04.563 --> 21:06.122
Oh, now, that's different, yeah.

21:06.265 --> 21:08.359
All right, I'll take
about a thousand of this one

21:08.501 --> 21:11.334
that says "I love you,
you are the only one."

21:11.470 --> 21:14.132
A thousand
"You're the only one"?

21:14.273 --> 21:15.934
That's right. I have this urge

21:16.075 --> 21:19.238
to spread hope
all over the world.

21:19.378 --> 21:21.813
Yeah. It's Joanie.
She's gonna...

21:21.947 --> 21:23.415
Kiss?

21:23.549 --> 21:24.812
<i>No, no, Joanna's gonna smoke.</i>

21:24.950 --> 21:26.213
Oh, smoke.

21:26.352 --> 21:27.751
All right,
I'll take care of this.

21:27.887 --> 21:29.116
No, Fonz, wait.

21:29.255 --> 21:31.223
You got
to let her handle this herself.

21:31.357 --> 21:33.485
I'll give her five seconds
to change her mind.

21:33.626 --> 21:35.617
All right, thanks.

21:37.163 --> 21:38.255
Here, Joanie, light up.

21:38.397 --> 21:40.593
I'll teach you how
to do the French inhale.

21:40.733 --> 21:42.724
Oh.

21:47.907 --> 21:49.966
Uh... no.

21:50.109 --> 21:52.100
I don't smoke.

21:54.947 --> 21:58.042
Why not? You chicken?

21:58.184 --> 21:59.913
No, I'm not chicken.

22:00.052 --> 22:01.520
I just don't want it.

22:01.654 --> 22:05.454
Well, come on, Joanie.
I mean, it's not too cool.

22:05.591 --> 22:08.185
Oh, well,
I've been thinking about cool,

22:08.327 --> 22:10.091
and I decided
everyone should decide

22:10.229 --> 22:11.993
what's best for themselves.

22:12.131 --> 22:14.293
And I don't think
smoking is cool.

22:16.669 --> 22:18.364
So, what do you say, Angela?

22:18.504 --> 22:21.633
Who do you want in the Magnets?
Me or my lungs?

22:21.774 --> 22:24.004
Take it easy, Joanie.
We-we want you.

22:24.143 --> 22:26.475
(Richie laughs quietly)

22:26.612 --> 22:29.047
Okay. No cigarettes.

22:29.181 --> 22:31.809
Boy, you got guts.
Wish I had.

22:31.951 --> 22:34.943
Maybe then I wouldn't be up
to two packs a day.

22:35.087 --> 22:38.352
I did save enough coupons to get
my dad a new bowling ball.

22:40.626 --> 22:44.256
Well, I proved one thing
to myself.

22:45.297 --> 22:47.561
Now I have to prove another.

22:50.603 --> 22:52.867
Uh... hi, Jim.

22:53.005 --> 22:54.336
Hi, Joanie.

22:54.473 --> 22:57.704
Uh, remember you told me
I was grown up because I smoked?

22:57.843 --> 22:59.140
Yeah?

22:59.278 --> 23:01.940
Uh, well, I don't smoke anymore.

23:02.081 --> 23:04.573
What do you say now?

23:04.717 --> 23:06.242
I was wrong.

23:06.385 --> 23:09.150
I... I guess...
it wasn't the cigarettes.

23:09.288 --> 23:10.517
- Uh.
- Want to dance?

23:10.656 --> 23:12.522
You bet.

23:12.658 --> 23:14.649
(slow instrumental music plays)

23:33.012 --> 23:35.003
(crickets chirping)

23:37.416 --> 23:39.282
Now I've made
my own decision now,

23:39.418 --> 23:41.648
and I've given up
smoking for good.

23:41.787 --> 23:44.882
Well, Joanie,
lam so proud of you.

23:45.024 --> 23:46.219
(Joanie chuckles softly)

23:46.358 --> 23:47.587
(phone ringing)

23:47.726 --> 23:50.058
You're gonna be a lot happier,
too, when you get older.

23:50.195 --> 23:51.720
